To compile (and produce LSSTreferences.pdf):
> make 


To add a new reference, add the BibTeX entry to LSSTbiblio.bib, and add a citation 
to the appropriate section of LSSTreferences.tex;  e.g.

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

@BOOK{RHLStatsBook,
   author = {{Lupton}, R.~H.},
    title = "{Statistics in theory and practice}",
publisher = {Princeton University Press},
     year = 1993,
   adsurl = {http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/1993stp..book.....L},
  adsnote = {Provided by the SAO/NASA Astrophysics Data System}
}

and

\cite{RHLStatsBook}

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

N.b. Please check that your BibTeX entry is written in ascii, some entries you find on 
the net use more general character sets.  The entry will probably work, but will 
generate complaints.
